            <abstract>
                <p> An author portrait, showing one of the four
                  Evangelists
                  (<persName ref="PRS6902Matthew">Matthew</persName>;
                  <persName ref="PRS6751Mark">Mark</persName>;
                  <persName ref="PRS6387Luke">Luke</persName>;
                  <persName ref="PRS5695John">John</persName>), 
                    typically placed opposite to the beginning of his text.
                    As in other traditions, the Evangelists perform a variety of actions, 
                    such as holding or writing the copy of their  
                    <title ref="LIT1560Gospel">Gospel</title>.
                    The two main typologies attested in the Ethiopian tradition are:
                    ① Type 1 ⇨ The Evangelist is depicted in a <term>seated</term> position.
                    ② Type 2 ⇨ The Evangelist is depicted in a <term>standing</term> position.
                  </p>
